    "body": "In C99 it's possible to create an array with a calculated length on the stack:\n\n\n```\nvoid f(int a) {\n    int size = a + 2;\n    char b[   ...\n}\n```\n\nIt would be great if Cython would support this as well. It would remove a lot of boilerplate code, because constructs like\n\n```\ncdef my_function(int length, object otherstuff):\n    cdef int *arr\n\n    arr = <int*> libc.malloc(length * sizeof(arr))\n    if arr is NULL:\n        raise SomeError()\n\n    try:\n       do_what_I_really_wanted_to_do()\n    finally:\n       libc.free(arr)\n```\n\nwould become the much more concise\n\n```\ncdef my_function(int length, object otherstuff):\n    cdef int arr[length](size];\n\n)\n\n    do_what_I_really_wanted_to_do()\n```\n\nMigrated from http://trac.cython.org/ticket/749",
